HEADWORD: Perimeter
<hw>Per*im"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>peri`</grk> around + <?/ measure: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧rim⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>The outer boundary of a body or figure, or the
sum of all the sides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for determining the extent and shape
of the field of vision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

